Sentencas: In this work, La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 (LSM/YSZ) composite nano-tubes are co-synthesized by a pore wetting technique as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of nano-tube and nano-rod structured La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A fast-firing method is introduced to improve the contact between the composite cathode and the YSZ electrolyte, as well as to retain the original nano-tube structure.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of nano-tube and nano-rod structured La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The morphology and structure studies indicate that the LSM/YSZ composite cathodes which undergo a 1100 degrees C heat treatment present nano-tube and nano-rod structure (with heating and cooling rates of 200 and 100 degrees C min(-1)).
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of nano-tube and nano-rod structured La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) of the composite cathodes is characterized by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of nano-tube and nano-rod structured La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The as-prepared nanostructured composite cathode shows low ASR values, which is mainly clue to small grain size, homogeneous particle distribution and fine pore structure of the material.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of nano-tube and nano-rod structured La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
